# Number of attributes (categories)
num_attributes = len(df)

# Create a list of attribute names and corresponding values
attributes = df['Percentage Percent of Dustbin 1'].tolist()
values = df['Percentage Percent of Dustbin 1.1'].tolist()

# Make sure the radar chart is closed (add the first attribute at the end)
attributes += attributes[:1]
values += values[:1]

# Create an array of angles for each axis
angles = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, num_attributes, endpoint=False).tolist()
angles += angles[:1]  # Close the chart

# Create the radar chart
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 8), subplot_kw={'polar': True})
ax.fill(angles, values, 'b', alpha=0.1)

# Set the title and labels for each axis
ax.set_title('Radar Chart')
ax.set_xticks(angles[:-1])
ax.set_xticklabels(attributes)
ax.set_yticklabels([])  # You can remove the y-axis labels if needed

# Fill the area under the radar lines
ax.fill(angles, values, 'b', alpha=0.1)

# Display the radar chart
plt.show()
